<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="320" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="47.[794,1399,425,865]" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,898,425,449]" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="FORSTER" authorityYear="1871" box="[905,1038,425,449]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectoralis">
<emphasis box="[905,1038,425,449]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">H. pectoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1272,425,449]" name="Turkey" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Turkey</collectingCountry>
for the first time. The species is well known as a user of vacated galls of the chloropid fly 
<taxonomicName authority="MEIGEN" authorityName="MEIGEN" box="[1009,1247,489,513]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Lipara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucens">
<emphasis box="[1009,1152,489,513]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Lipara lucens</emphasis>
MEIGEN
</taxonomicName>
in reed stems (
<taxonomicName box="[803,1022,521,545]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phragmites" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="47" pageNumber="320" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[803,1022,521,545]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Phragmites australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It nests in the abandoned galls and is therefore confined to wetlands with stands of reeds. The collecting site in 
<collectingRegion box="[1101,1199,586,609]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Erzurum</collectingRegion>
is a narrow valley containing pastureland, through which a stream flows, a branch of the river Çoruh, beside which are small 
<taxonomicName box="[794,912,681,705]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Phragmites" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="47" pageNumber="320" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[794,912,681,705]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Phragmites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
patches.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[794,1399,425,865]" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">
In agreement with the general situation for this species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="FORSTER" authorityYear="1871" box="[794,928,745,769]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectoralis">
<emphasis box="[794,928,745,769]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">H. pectoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows a limited, disjunctive distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[794,871,777,801]" name="Turkey" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. Hitherto, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="FORSTER" authorityYear="1871" box="[994,1128,777,801]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectoralis">
<emphasis box="[994,1128,777,801]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">H. pectoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found at four places in 
<collectingRegion box="[896,994,810,833]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Erzurum</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1049,1118,809,833]" country="Turkey" name="Mugla" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Muğla</collectingRegion>
only. It is rarely recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[822,898,841,865]" name="Turkey" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(2 provinces, 
<figureCitation box="[1052,1149,841,865]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="68.[212,245,807,829]" captionTargetBox="[212,1422,233,796]" captionTargetId="figure-236@68.[212,1422,233,796]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="Fig. 16: Distribution map of newly recorded Hylaeus species in Turkey." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742933" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742933/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Figs 16.7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1161,1189,841,865]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="68.[211,244,1429,1451]" captionTargetBox="[211,1414,859,1420]" captionTargetId="figure-259@68.[211,1414,859,1420]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="Fig. 17: Distribution map of rarely recorded Hylaeus species in Turkey: species collected in only one (1-12) or two (II-X)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742935/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">17</figureCitation>
.IV).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="320" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="47.[794,1399,905,1025]" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,941,905,929]" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Distribution:</emphasis>
Transpalaearctic from the Pyrenees to 
<collectingCountry box="[794,857,938,961]" name="Japan" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Japan</collectingCountry>
, but because of its specific ecological requirements only locally recorded. 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1225,969,993]" name="Turkey" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Turkey</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[1244,1342,970,993]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Erzurum</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[794,866,1001,1025]" country="Turkey" name="Mugla" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">Muğla</collectingRegion>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[876,1159,1001,1025]" pageId="47" pageNumber="320">New to the Turkish fauna</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
